Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The directory to check.
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - The number of children.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success - The operation succeeded.

Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. 687b66cd-6878-4ae8-8fad-fa315ef08955.b0dae14d-b71c-4078-8fb6-fe7a882cd97e.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
687b66cd-6878-4ae8-8fad-fa315ef08955.b85c1e4b-1968-4ed0-b528-644530bdb4d7.transition.description=processing ${current}. 687b66cd-6878-4ae8-8fad-fa315ef08955.dab1c9ed-d58a-4821-8273-035045fd7cb1.description=For an unknown reason the subdirectory could not be traversed. 687b66cd-6878-4ae8-8fad-fa315ef08955.dab1c9ed-d58a-4821-8273-035045fd7cb1.prompt=For an unknown reason the subdirectory could not be traversed. 687b66cd-6878-4ae8-8fad-fa315ef08955.description=
This flow demonstrates how to traverse a directory tree.

Inputs\:
    source - The directory to get the children of.
    delimiter - A delimiter to put in between each child of this directory.
Default value\: , (comma).
    username - The username to traverse directories as.
    password - The password for username.

Responses\:
    success - The sample completed successfully. Directory was traversed without error.
    failure - The sample failed. Possible causes are\: unable to login to host, bad directory name, filesystem error.

Note\:
    The flow will go through every sub folder of the source. If you set source to a folder with many children (such as c\:\ on a windows system) then it will take this flow a long time to complete.
